text: Roman Catholic church Velké Karlovice is a village in Vsetín District, Zlín Region, Czech Republic. It has a population of 2,680 (2005). It was founded in 1714. The village lies on the Vsetínská Bečva river. The Czech-Slovak remake of the British TV series 'Doctor Martin' was filmed in Velké Karlovice. == External links == * Official website Category:Villages in Vsetín District Category:1714 establishments in the Holy Roman Empire Category:Moravian Wallachia
